Package: mesh_process
Type: Package
Title: An R tool for batch-processing of meshes and landmark files for shape analyses
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: c(person("Marta", "Vidal-Garcia", email = "marta.vidalga@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")), person("Hallgrimsson", "Benedikt", role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Marta Vidal-Garcia <marta.vidalga@gmail.com>
Description: Here we provide several functions that batch import, process (by reducing the number of faces, closing holes, removing isolated pieces, etc. as per the R package Rvcg), and save multiple meshes in different formats (e.g. PLY, STL, VTK). It also allows batch-importing and saving landmark files in differnt formats (*.aim, *.tag, *.mps, etc.).
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports: rgl,
  Rvcg,
  freesurferformats
License: GPL (>=2)
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/marta-vidalgarcia/mesh_process
BugReports: https://github.com/marta-vidalgarcia/mesh_process/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
